<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900517-0058</DOCNO><DOCID>900517-0058.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Owens-Illinois Inc.:   Loss Narrowed in 1st Period   On 11% Revenue Increase</HL><DATE>05/17/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A13</SO><CO>   OI</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Owens-Illinois Inc., taken private in a leveraged buy-outin 1987, reported a narrower first-quarter net loss on 11%higher revenue, sending its publicly traded bonds higher.   All of the company's major businesses -- glass containers,plastics and closures, specialized glass and health care --posted &quot;strong&quot; performances, Owens-Illinois said in aSecurities and Exchange Commission filing.</LP><TEXT>   The Toledo, Ohio, company, taken private in 1987 for $3.64billion by Kohlberg Kravis Roberts andamp; Co., reported itsdeficit shrank to $12.3 million, or 33 cents a share, from$32.3 million, or 87 cents a share, a year earlier. Revenuerose to $956.3 million from $855.4 million.   Owens-Illinois's earnings before depreciation,amortization, interest and tax rose 29% to $192.2 millionfrom $149.5 million. And interest coverage -- the number oftimes these earnings exceed interest expense -- increased to1.46 from 1.22.</TEXT></DOC>